  - `data/reports/section_7_exp.md`
  - `data/reports/section_8_prod.md`
  - `data/reports/section_8_exp.md`
  - `data/reports/section_10_prod.md`
  - `data/reports/section_10_exp.md`
- Barrel sections:
  - `data/reports/section_11.md`
  - `data/reports/section_12.md`
  - `data/reports/section_13.md`
  - `data/reports/sections_11_13.md`
- Archive:
  - `data/reports/archive/<slate_date>/...` copies of generated artifacts

## Chat Deliverable Rules

- **ALWAYS print Section 0 (drift + bucket health) at the very top of the daily output.** This is the trust meter — read it first.
- **ALWAYS print Section 14 (Conviction Picks) at the bottom.** This is the betting deliverable, filtered to M1 Lock picks only.
- Print sections in chat for all sections except 7, 8, and 10.
- Keep sections 7, 8, and 10 in markdown files only (do not paste those writeups in chat unless explicitly asked).
- Show production and experiment outputs side-by-side for the probability table sections (1-6), using the same column schema as project rules:
  - Adj probability, raw probability, 3-PA probability, confidence score, confidence label, and BvP/career context columns as applicable.
- Also include three dedicated side-by-side comparison tables in chat for:
  - Home Runs (top 25 by raw `p_hr`)
  - Hits (top 25 by raw `p_hit`)
  - XBH (top 25 by raw `p_xbh`)
- Dedicated comparison table format must be:
  - `# | Model 1 batter | Conf | vs SP | Model 2 batter | Conf | vs SP`
  - Where `Model 1` = production, `Model 2` = experiment.
  - `vs SP` format: `H/AB, XB<n>, HR<n>`; use `—` if no BvP PA exists.
- After each dedicated comparison table, include a short comparison block with:
  - overlap count, model-only counts, average raw-probability gap on overlaps, and notable movers/new entries.
- Include Section 9 and Sections 11-13 in chat.
- Confirm where files were saved.
